name: overview-and-detail-documentation-best-practices.mdc
description: Best practices for structuring overview and detailed Markdown documents
globs: "*.md"

- Overview documents (Project.md, README.md):
  - Describe the project's overall purpose and goals
  - List main components and their relationships
  - Reference detailed documents with links
  - Outline the overall workflow
  - Describe high-level system architecture

- Detailed documents (Instruction.md, API_Docs.md, etc.):
  - Focus on a specific component or function
  - Provide detailed requirements and specifications
  - Include links back to the overview document
  - Use illustrative examples (not code)
  - Define constraints and relationships with other components 